The blockchain pruning pull request has been merged! 🎉    https://t.co/xMT0tjtsUk  In Monero, blockchain pruning is somewhat different insofar as 1/8th of the full blockchain is still retained. Thus, a pruned node can still (partly) serve other nodes.

Nonetheless, the size on disk reduction is significant. That is, a pruned blockchain file is approximately 23 GB, whereas a full blockchain file is currently approximately 70 GB. A stellar reduction of about 2/3rd is thus achieved.
